parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Accusative Neuter Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.
Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 1st Person Plural
str2: Trans: To hold before; mid: To excuse myself; intrans: To project, excel, surpass, have preeminence.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.
Wholly, entirely, in every way, by all means, certainly. Adverb from pas; entirely; specially, at all events, in no event.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

word: we have already made the charge
parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Middle - 1st Person Plural
str2: To make a prior accusation. From pro and a derivative of aitia; to accuse already, i.e. Previously charge.
Jewish. From Iouda; Judaean, i.e. Belonging to Jehudah.
From Hellas; a Hellen or inhabitant of Hellas; by extension a Greek-speaking person, especially a non-Jew.
And, both. A primary particle of connection or addition; both or also.
I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.
A primary preposition; under, i.e. of place, or with verbs; of place (underneath) or where (below) or time (when).
